  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/63719511" />
    <a title="Dawn" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/965367-dawn"><img alt="Dawn" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1210467294p2/965367.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/63719511?book_show_action=true">Jul 16, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dawn" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dawn" href="/user/show/965367-dawn">Dawn</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/965367-dawn?shelf=own">own</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/965367-dawn?shelf=book-club-selection">book-club-selection</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer63719511" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9829853165428152930">Let&apos;s be honest. I will probably never pick up this book to finish it. I began reading this because of my book club. But, I didn&apos;t think I would finish it to begin with, and due to many circumstances, the book club will not be meeting for this book. So, I have decided to put it down as one of those books I&apos;ll never finish.<br/><br/>I didn&apos;t like most of what I read, not due to the subject/topic, but due to the way Pinker writes. His droning on on tangents and his shoving his philosophy, which is oh so rig</span>
  <span id="freeText9829853165428152930" style="display:none">Let's be honest. I will probably never pick up this book to finish it. I began reading this because of my book club. But, I didn't think I would finish it to begin with, and due to many circumstances, the book club will not be meeting for this book. So, I have decided to put it down as one of those books I'll never finish.<br /><br />I didn't like most of what I read, not due to the subject/topic, but due to the way Pinker writes. His droning on on tangents and his shoving his philosophy, which is oh so right BTW [she said dripping with sarcasm:] was too much for me. I had a hard time staying interested, which was a shame, because most sections began with promise. But Pinker would, more often than not, find a way to make the topic at hand induce heavy eyelids (or eye rolling, depending).<br /><br />I wanted this book to be good and thought it would be interesting, being a Bachelor of Psychology graduate myself, but no such luck. Maybe in many years, when I have more time on my hands, or less sense, I will try picking this book up again.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9829853165428152930" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


